1 (5) The Secretary of State shall require that each person employed in the Office of the
2 Secretary of State directly responsible for the administration of the Safe at Home
3 Program submit his or her fingerprints to the Department of State. The Department
4 of State shall exchange fingerprint data with the Kentucky State Police and the
5 Federal Bureau of Investigation in order to conduct a criminal history background
6 check of each employee directly responsible for the administration of the program.
7 Section 2. KRS 14.304 is amended to read as follows:
8 (1) Upon the creation of the Safe at Home Program, the following individuals may
9 apply to the Secretary of State to have an address designated as his or her mailing
10 address in place of his or her residential address:
11 (a) An adult victim;
12 (b) A parent or guardian acting on behalf of a minor when the minor resides with
13 him or her;
14 (c) A guardian acting on behalf of an incapacitated individual who is a victim of a
15 specified offense;[ and]
16 (d) Any individuals residing with the victim; and
17 (e) Anyone identified in subsection (2)(b) to (f) of Section 1 of this Act.
18 (2) The Secretary of State shall approve an application if it is filed in the manner and
19 on the form prescribed by the Secretary of State and if it contains:
20 (a) 1. For victims, a sworn statement, under penalty of perjury, by the
21 applicant that:
22 a.[1.] The applicant is a victim of a specified offense or resides in the
23 same household as a victim of a specified offense;
24 b.[2]. The applicant fears for his or her own safety or the safety of
25 another person who resides in the same household; and
26 c.[3.] The applicant is not applying for certification as a program
27 participant in order to avoid prosecution for a crime; or
Page 2 of 10
HB044210.100 - 1826 - XXXX 3/17/2026 4:10 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 442/GA
1 2. For anyone identified in subsection (2)(b) to (f) of Section 1 of this
2 Act, a sworn statement, under penalty of perjury, by the applicant that:
3 a. He or she is qualified to request to participate in the program
4 under Section 1 of this Act; and
5 b. He or she desires to be a part of the program;
6 (b) The mailing address and the phone number or numbers where the applicant
7 can be contacted by the Secretary of State or the Secretary of State's designee;
8 (c) The new address or addresses that the applicant requests not be disclosed for
9 the reason that disclosure will increase the risk of a specified offense,
10 jeopardize the applicant's safety, or increase the risk of violence to the
11 applicant or members of the applicant's household;
12 (d) The date the application was prepared, the applicant's signature, and, if
13 applicable, the signature of the application assistant who assisted the applicant
14 in applying to be a program participant; and
15 (e) A designation of the Secretary of State as agent for purposes of service of
16 process and for receipt of first class mail, legal documents, and certified mail.
17 (3) Applications shall be filed with the Office of the Secretary of State. Applicants may
18 choose to consult with an application assistant for assistance with the application
19 process or apply online directly through the portal designated by the Secretary of
20 State.
21 (4) Upon the filing of a properly completed application, the Secretary of State shall
22 certify the applicant as a program participant if the applicant is not required to
23 register as a sex offender or is not otherwise prohibited from participating in the
24 program.
25 (5) Applicants shall be certified for four (4) years following the date of filing unless the
26 certification is withdrawn or invalidated before that date. The Secretary of State
27 shall send notification of an expiring certification and a renewal form to a program
Page 3 of 10
HB044210.100 - 1826 - XXXX 3/17/2026 4:10 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 442/GA
1 participant at least four (4) weeks prior to the expiration of the program participant's
2 certification. The renewal need only be signed by the applicant and need not be
3 made before an application assistant. The Secretary of State shall promulgate an
4 administrative regulation to establish a renewal procedure.
5 (6) A person who falsely attests in an application that disclosure of the address of the
6 applicant would endanger the safety of the applicant or the safety of the children of
7 the applicant, or the minor or incompetent person on whose behalf the application is
8 made, or household members residing with the applicant, or who knowingly
9 provides false or incorrect information upon making an application may be found
10 guilty of a violation of KRS 523.030.
11 (7) The addresses of individuals applying for entrance into the Safe at Home Program
12 and the addresses of those certified as program participants shall be exempt from
13 disclosure under the Kentucky Open Records Act, KRS 61.870 to KRS 61.884. An
14 agency may not require the program participant to submit any new address that
15 could be used to physically locate the participant. When creating a new public
16 record, state and local agencies shall accept the address designated by the Secretary
17 of State as a program participant's substitute address, unless the Secretary of State
18 has determined that:
19 (a) The agency has a bona fide statutory or administrative requirement for the use
20 of the address which would otherwise be confidential under this chapter; and
21 (b) This address will be used only for those statutory and administrative purposes.
22 (8) (a) As part of the application process established by the Secretary of State
23 pursuant to subsections (1) and (2) of this section, an applicant may request
24 that state or local agencies be notified that an applicant has been certified and
25 enrolled in the Safe at Home Program.
26 (b) 1. The Secretary of State shall provide to such agencies the address that
27 has been designated by the Secretary of State to serve as the mailing
