1 address of the participant;
2 2. Agencies receiving such notification from the Secretary of State shall
3 change any existing records to reflect the new address submitted under
4 subparagraph 1. of this paragraph;
5 3. Notifications under this section shall not affect residency designations;
6 and
7 4. Subparagraph 2. of this paragraph shall not apply to paper records if
8 such records are more than five (5) years old and would be under the
9 normal course of business maintained or archived in the event of an
10 address change.
11 (9) Except as provided for in subsection (10) of this section, if a program participant
12 has notified a person in writing that he or she is a program participant, that person
13 shall not knowingly disclose the program participant's:
14 (a) Name;
15 (b) Home address;
16 (c) Work address; or
17 (d) School address.
18 (10) Any person to whom a program participant has provided written notification that he
19 or she is a program participant may knowingly disclose the program participant's
20 name, and home, work, or school address if that person also lives, works, or goes to
21 school at the address disclosed, or the participant has provided written consent to
22 disclosure of the participant's name, home, work, or school address, for the purpose
23 for which the disclosure will be made.
24 (11) A program participant shall notify the Office of the Secretary of State of a change
25 of address within fourteen (14) days of the change of address.
26 (12) The Secretary of State shall provide verification of an individual's enrollment in the
27 Safe at Home Program, as well as a personalized Safe at Home Program card. The
