1 Safe at Home Program verification card shall contain the participant's name,
2 substitute address as designated by the Secretary of State, and any additional
3 information as determined necessary to include by the Secretary of State.
4 (13) Any person relocating or doing business in the Commonwealth of Kentucky who is
5 a participant in a program in another state that is similar to the Safe at Home
6 Program shall be deemed approved for inclusion in the Commonwealth of
7 Kentucky's program for one (1) year. The Secretary of State shall promulgate
8 administrative regulations establishing procedures necessary to recognize similar
9 programs from outside the Commonwealth of Kentucky and enroll their
10 participants. The following exceptions shall apply:
11 (a) If the person is temporarily residing in the Commonwealth of Kentucky, he or
12 she shall be considered a participant in the Safe at Home Program as long as
13 he or she continues participation in such a program of a home state; or
14 (b) If the person is not residing in the Commonwealth of Kentucky but is doing
15 business or engaged in other transactions there, the person shall be considered
16 a participant in the Safe at Home Program as long as he or she continues to
17 participate in a similar program in his or her state of residence.
18 Section 3. KRS 118.125 is amended to read as follows:
19 (1) Except as provided in KRS 118.155, any person who is qualified under the
20 provisions of KRS 116.055 to vote in any primary for the candidates for nomination
21 by the party at whose hands he or she seeks the nomination, shall have his or her
22 name printed on the official ballot of his or her party for an office to which he or
23 she is eligible in that primary, upon filing, with the Secretary of State or county
24 clerk, as appropriate, at the proper time, a notification and declaration.
25 (2) The notification and declaration shall be in the form prescribed by the State Board
26 of Elections. It shall be signed by the candidate and by not less than two (2)
27 registered voters, who at the time of signing are of the same party as the candidate
Page 6 of 10
HB044210.100 - 1826 - XXXX 3/17/2026 4:10 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 442/GA
1 and from the district or jurisdiction from which the candidate seeks nomination.
2 Signatures for nomination papers shall not be affixed on the document to be filed
3 prior to the first Wednesday after the first Monday in November of the year
4 preceding the year in which the office will appear on the ballot. The notification
5 and declaration for a candidate shall include the following oath:
6 "For the purpose of having my name placed on the official primary election
7 ballot as a candidate for nomination by the ------ Party, I, ------ (name in full as
8 desired on the ballot as provided in KRS 118.129), do solemnly swear that my date
9 of birth is ----- (month/day/year), that my residence address is ----- (street, route,
10 highway, city if applicable, county, state, and zip code), that my mailing address, if
11 different, is ----- (post office address), and that I am a registered ------ (party) voter;
12 that I believe in the principles of the ------ Party, and intend to support its principles
13 and policies; that I meet all the statutory and constitutional qualifications for the
14 office which I am seeking; that if nominated as a candidate of such party at the
15 ensuing election I will accept the nomination and not withdraw for reasons other
16 than those stated in KRS 118.105(3); that I will not knowingly violate any election
17 law or any law relating to corrupt and fraudulent practice in campaigns or elections
18 in this state, and if finally elected I will qualify for the office."
19 The declaration shall be subscribed and sworn to before an officer authorized to
20 administer an oath by the candidate and by the two (2) voters making the
21 declaration and signing the candidate's petition for office. The two (2) voters
22 making the declaration and signing the candidate's petition for office shall not be
23 participants in the Safe at Home Program under KRS 14.300 to 14.318. However,
24 the signature of a Safe at Home Program participant shall not invalidate the
25 candidate's filing, shall not disqualify the candidate from appearing on the ballot,
26 and shall not constitute grounds for challenging the candidate's nomination or
27 election.
