1 (3) When the notice and declaration has been filed with the Secretary of State or county
2 clerk, as appropriate, and certified according to KRS 118.165, the Secretary of State
3 or county clerk, as appropriate, shall have the candidate's name printed on the ballot
4 according to the provisions of this chapter, except as provided in KRS 118.185.
5 (4) Titles, ranks, or spurious phrases shall not be accepted on the filing papers and shall
6 not be printed on the ballots as part of the candidate's name; however, nicknames,
7 initials, and contractions of given names may be acceptable as the candidate's name.
8 Section 4. KRS 118A.060 is amended to read as follows:
9 (1) Except as provided in KRS 118A.100, no person's name shall appear on a ballot,
10 including an absentee ballot, for an office of the Court of Justice without first
11 having been nominated as provided in this section.
12 (2) Each candidate for nomination shall file a petition for nomination with the
13 Secretary of State not earlier than the first Wednesday after the first Monday in
14 November of the year preceding the year in which the office will appear on the
15 ballot and not later than the first Friday following the first Monday in January
16 preceding the day fixed by law for holding the primary for the office. The petition
17 shall be sworn to before an officer authorized to administer an oath by the candidate
18 and by not less than two (2) registered voters from the district or circuit from which
19 he or she seeks nomination. The two (2) voters making the declaration and signing
20 the candidate's petition for office shall not be participants in the Safe at Home
21 Program under KRS 14.300 to 14.318. However, the signature of a Safe at Home
22 Program participant shall not invalidate the candidate's filing, shall not
23 disqualify the candidate from appearing on the ballot, and shall not constitute
24 grounds for challenging the candidate's nomination or election. Signatures for
25 nomination papers shall not be affixed on the document to be filed prior to the first
26 Wednesday after the first Monday in November of the year preceding the year in
27 which the office will appear on the ballot. The petition shall be filed no later than 4
